			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65028397"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65028397"><p>The reason they go with the "personal names" for voice assistants is mostly to prevent triggering the wake words from normal speech when not wanted.  Anyone with a voice capable device is familiar with them turning on when you don't want, but if the wake word is something like "Jarvis" then that's a word that doesn't sound like something that would be said in normal speech.</p><p>To their credit, you can define a custom wake word for  the new box, you just need to train the model for it</p></div>
	</div>

